 learning through its focus on anti-discriminatory practice in a climate that appears less sympathetic to the multicultural nature of British society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBlacksxServices forzGreat Britain. 0aBlacksxServices forzUnited States. 0aSocial work with minoritieszGreat Britain. 0aSocial work with minoritieszUnited States. 0aSocial work with minorities. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aColby, Ira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978186134845640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447342533423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447342533/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles